methods: (function) that is a block of code performing a specific task,
          runs only when it's called(invoked)
          -> grouping a set of code fragment that can perform a specific task
          why: code reusability
               improved modularity
               improved readability
               easier to maintain

two categories:
                - standard library methods:
                    - already build in java (main() etc.)

                - user-defined methods:
                   - created by yourself
