Return Value:
=> a way to provide a result or an output from the method back to the code that called it


           return type
public static  int addNumbers(int num1, int, num2 ){
       int sum = num1 + num2;
       return sum; //resturns sum of nums }

- method call will give me a data,
    can be treated as value and can be stored into a variable if needed
    method call can be passed on to print statement
- whenever retun method is called a new data will be returned again


==>> RULES:
            - declare return type in method header to specify type of value that method will return
            - use return keyword followed by value that we want returned
            - if method has void return type, no value is returned
            - after return statement , no code will be executed
            - a method can have multiple return statements inside the conditional statement, but only one will eb executed
